My take on the Left 4 Dead 1 Apartment level. The architecture is the same but the layout and flow have been redone for play with Counter Strike Source Zombie Mod. Added in several teleports and hidden walls plus couches and soda machines for making barricades. I went for this location for this map as most ZM maps seem to be too bright and I wanted something a little darker. This map has 50 total spawn points, 25 for each side. Originally had a lot of the L4D artwork and signs/graffiti in here but removed them to keep potential copyright problems from popping up.
I made a video highlighting most of the hidden stuff. Some things I added in after feedback from friends so not everything is in this video.
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=01RbmFUxuhI
Any feedback or ideas, let me know.
Thanks in advance!

Goal:

Make your way to the higher floors, barricade or find a perfect place for camping and protecting yourself from zombies, while waiting 2:30 min for the crane to lower a platform on which you need to get on to escape! The crane will take you to a building's roof, where you can launch a nuke :P

---
Feautures:

- Destroyable stairs
- Destroyable floors
- Crane
- Enough places to camp at, while waiting the crane
- Big bad nuke boom!
- Secret chamber :D
---

-FAQ-

Q: I was too late to get on the platform, what now?
A: Welcome to hell.

Q: Nobody got on the platform, what now?
A: You still can protect yourself ON the construction site, and you still can win, because nobody will push the nuke button.

Q: Do humans have any chances to win?
A: Yes, maybe even more than zombies. Humans can break the floor, stairs. That will make zombie's life harder. Humans also can easily shoot zombies off the poles without any floor on it. So, you have to destroy the floor as fast as you can.

Mapping & Ideas by: kamikaze|deadeye`

Cannon by: #NeutraLized



This is the second release.


_________
|*Fixed*|
-----------

-There was an issue with people getting stuck in teleports due to heavy player loads; This has been fixed and should no longer be a problem.

-An area where CT's had a BIG advantage has been modified to even out the game play, zombies should have a good chance now.

-An elevator has been upgraded with doors so you can no longer be shot off.

-1 room has been totally re-done to add to the game play.

-More props have been added to provide better barricades.

-The spawn has been split into two areas to help disperse people around the map.
